1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:02,440
Uh, Grandma…

2
00:00:03,520 --> 00:00:05,440
There's something I'd like to talk about.

3
00:00:08,160 --> 00:00:10,560
It's about this painting.

4
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:18,080
Who allowed you
to bring this painting back here?

5
00:00:18,720 --> 00:00:22,280
I know
that Mr. Wichan painted this picture.

6
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:25,240
And the woman in the painting

7
00:00:25,840 --> 00:00:28,440
is Ms. Ampha and her daughter.

8
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:31,520
Who gave you permission
to talk about such things in my house?

9
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,880
Please, Grandma.

10
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,520
Please help Ms. Ampha.

11
00:02:58,040 --> 00:03:00,760
The reason Ms. Ampha ended up like this
is because of me.

12
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:01,760
Boonsita.

13
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:05,640
If you still refuse to stop
bringing up that woman's name,

14
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,840
you will no longer stay in this house.

15
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:10,960
But the little girl in the painting

16
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:13,240
- is your granddaughter, Grandma.
- Stop right now.

17
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,320
Do you still not understand
that I don't want to hear it?

18
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:19,760
The reason Ms. Ampha
is still wandering like this,

19
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,840
I believe,

20
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:22,600
it's because of her daughter.

21
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,600
Grandma,

22
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:27,360
you're the one who knows everything.

23
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:30,280
If you don't want to help, that's fine.

24
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,680
But can you at least tell me
about Ms. Ampha?

25
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,680
Those two.

26
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,280
That mother and child

27
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,720
are dead.

28
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:47,920
Supol investigated it himself and told me.

29
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,080
Then did Mr. Supol

30
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:54,440
see their bodies?

31
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,560
Are you accusing me of lying?

32
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,920
No, Grandma.

33
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,520
I'm just wondering.

34
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:05,640
How can you be so sure
that they are really dead,

35
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:08,200
when no one has ever seen Ms. Ampha's body

36
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,200
or her daughter's?

37
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,880
What makes you so certain

38
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,760
that Ampha and Waree are dead,

39
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,760
when no one has seen their bodies?

40
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:18,240
So you think I'm lying, Wichan?

41
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,040
Grandma, are you alright?

42
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,800
I'm fine. I'm fine.

43
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,640
Do you think

44
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:58,360
I don't want to see my granddaughter?

45
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:02,000
I never

46
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:06,000
wanted things to end up like this either.

47
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:11,360
But why? Why…

48
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:16,480
Why does no one ever understand me?

49
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:43,120
Why does the car have to
break down now? Auntie's here too.

50
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:46,320
I really wanted to drive you home.

51
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,080
But look. Ugh.

52
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,400
Ow.

53
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:51,360
Stop acting.

54
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,240
Give me my phone back.

55
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:56,680
Your phone?

56
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,880
It's in the car. You can just take it.

57
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,560
If I could, I would have taken it already.

58
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:03,800
Your car is locked.

59
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:05,960
Oh.

60
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:08,360
Sorry. I've unlocked it now.

61
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:18,560
I'm sorry you have to
take a taxi home by yourself.

62
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,600
You can stop now. She already left.

63
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:34,920
Everything on my side is done.

64
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,600
Anong has taken a taxi home.
How about your side, Arnon?

65
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,080
Have you found Mr. Warat yet?

66
00:06:56,560 --> 00:07:00,360
Mr. Warat, where have you been?
Do you know something serious happened?

67
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:02,760
Mr. Supol already told me.
Grandma is always like this.

68
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,880
When she can't find a way out,
she pretends to be sick.

69
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,440
But it's not just that.

70
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:12,320
Ms. Ampha made me see
that her daughter is still alive.

71
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,600
And the other child?

72
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,280
I couldn't see.

73
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:22,360
But I'm certain
that girl is not some energy or spirit.

74
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,200
She's a real person.

75
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,160
What's going on today?

76
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,640
What I faced was already serious enough,

77
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:32,880
but this…

78
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,280
Where did you go?

79
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:37,920
What happened?

80
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,080
Auntie.

81
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:56,120
Auntie, where were you?
I couldn't reach you.

82
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:59,120
Sin, is there someone named Som
at your office?

83
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,480
Som? Yes.

84
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:02,760
Yes, Auntie.

85
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:04,840
I'm going to kill her.

86
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,720
That wretched girl.

87
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,000
You mean Som, Kluay's sister?

88
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,000
What did you say?

89
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:18,720
Those two are sisters?

90
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:25,360
I won't let you have a next time.

91
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,400
Auntie, I think

92
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:32,120
we should go eat something outside today.

93
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:34,000
- Don't work anymore. Come with me.
- Sin.

94
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:38,280
Don't you want to hear what Som did to me?

95
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:41,120
- Don't you want to hear it?
- Auntie, I do.

96
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,520
But I want you to calm down first.

97
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:45,320
Your hands are shaking,
your lips are pale.

98
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,800
Let's go get something to eat.

99
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:49,040
Please, Auntie. If she
really did something to you,

100
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,400
I won't let her get away with it.

101
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:52,360
Please, Auntie.

102
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,840
I swear

103
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,480
you won't need to do anything yourself.

104
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:04,200
Auntie, you're so small.
What could you possibly do to anyone?

105
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:05,200
Hm?

106
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:07,840
Let's go. Let's go eat.

107
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:10,720
Go change into something nice first.
Let's go.

108
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:16,640
I can't, Sin. In a moment,

109
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:19,120
I have to cook for Uncle Rut.

110
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:20,720
Alright?

111
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:26,760
Uh… Aunt Nong. Aunt Nong.

112
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,280
Oh?

113
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,640
Where did my glasses go?

114
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:01,400
- Hello?
<i>- I'm from the DNA center.</i>

115
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:04,560
You can come pick up the evidence now.

116
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:07,720
I've prepared everything for both parties.

117
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:11,120
<i>Alright. Our staff is on the way</i>
<i>to collect it.</i>

118
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,520
Okay. Thank you very much.

119
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:16,720
Let's see how this turns out.

120
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,200
Hey.

121
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:24,640
I tried focusing and touching it,
but I didn't see anything at all.

122
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,280
That's okay.

123
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:27,680
Well.

124
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,040
Uh, wait.

125
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:32,840
Actually, thinking about it again,
maybe it's nothing.

126
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:36,080
Maybe Mr. Sarut just
still misses your mother,

127
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,560
so he kept everything.

128
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:39,440
Oh, okay.

129
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,560
Where are you rushing off to?

130
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:46,720
Is there something
you still haven't told me?

131
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:50,800
No. Someone is coming
to pick up documents. I have to go now.

132
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:52,960
Hey.

133
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:54,960
Huh?

134
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,760
Can you put
the branch issue aside for now?

135
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:43,480
Right now, I want you to invite
your psychiatrist friend over.

136
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:44,800
Maybe just for dinner.

137
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,320
Aunt Nong refuses to go to the hospital.

138
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:50,320
I've tried tricking her,
but no matter what, she won't go.

139
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:55,000
Yes, it's urgent. If it wasn't,
would I be calling like this?

140
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,160
- If we leave it like this…
- Sin.

141
00:11:57,480 --> 00:12:00,920
Good. Then keep following up on it.

142
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:04,000
Alright, that's it. Okay.

143
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:06,080
Is something wrong?

144
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:10,240
Well… my room has been searched.

145
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:14,040
Uncle Rut probably went in
and searched it again.

146
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:15,800
It wasn't Uncle Rut.

147
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:17,880
Ever since I left the room unlocked,

148
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:20,040
Uncle Rut stopped suspecting me.

149
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:25,080
That bastard. It has to be him.

150
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,680
Who are you talking about?

151
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,160
Today I saw Warat at our house.

152
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,760
Why… why didn't you tell me?

153
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:36,840
You kept going on about

154
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:39,520
killing Kluay and Som.

155
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:41,200
When was I supposed to tell you?

156
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:43,560
Som…

157
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,640
It must be them working together.

158
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:49,680
Because of Som,

159
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:52,400
I didn't come back home.

160
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,240
So it gave him a chance
to break in and search the house.

161
00:12:57,960 --> 00:13:01,080
Did they… did they take anything?

162
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:04,480
Nothing is missing from my room.

163
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:07,640
Yes. Something important.

164
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:20,120
The photo of Praewilai and Warat.

165
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:22,600
Are you sure?

166
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:25,080
I saw it with my own eyes.

167
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:33,520
All set. The evidence
will reach the lab within the hour.

168
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:35,240
I need the results as soon as possible.

169
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,480
Yes, sir.

170
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:38,840
A DNA lab?

171
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,960
I can tell what they do from the name.

172
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:42,400
So no need to ask.

173
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:43,440
Mr. Warat,

174
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:45,720
what exactly are you doing?

175
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:48,480
I'm going to run a DNA test
between me and Mr. Sarut.

176
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:51,080
Mr. Warat, is it…?

177
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,760
Something doesn't add up.

178
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:59,000
I… I want to be sure.

179
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:01,440
I want to know how he's connected to me

180
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:03,000
and how he's related to my mother.

181
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:06,240
But are you sure
you can accept the answer?

182
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,960
The way you're saying that

183
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:12,520
means you're thinking the same as me.

184
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,840
Maybe you already have the answer,

185
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:19,240
you just won't say it.
Why won't you say it?

186
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:22,000
If you're worried about me, don't be.

187
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:25,880
Can you stop assuming the worst about me?

188
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:27,800
My vision isn't clear

189
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:31,320
to say exactly how Mr. Sarut
is connected to you or your mother.

190
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:33,480
See? You're still not
telling me everything.

191
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,960
Okay, from what I saw,

192
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:42,440
Mr. Sarut argued
about Ms. Praewilai's unborn child.

193
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:45,880
Then who else could that child be?

194
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,760
My mother only had me.

195
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,920
But it's still not clear

196
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:54,480
who Mr. Sarut really is.

197
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:59,120
I'm tired of all this uncertainty.

198
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:00,600
It's fine.

199
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:02,960
Once the DNA results are out,

200
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:04,920
we'll know.

201
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:08,600
No need to trouble you.

202
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:14,800
What are you looking at?

203
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,160
Mr. Warat.

204
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:23,320
Thank you for doing this.

205
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:28,280
You went into that house to find evidence
about who drugged me and Mr. Arnon.

206
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:31,600
But you ended up
getting caught in something else.

207
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:34,520
Anong is very careful.

208
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:37,240
She doesn't leave any evidence behind.

209
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,600
But I'm certain…

210
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,360
Ms. Anong is the one who drugged us.

211
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:47,000
Why would she want to kill you

212
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,960
and Mr. Arnon?

213
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:52,400
No.

214
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,840
Mr. Arnon
was just caught in the crossfire.

215
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:59,640
The one she really wanted to kill

216
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:01,680
was me.

217
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,640
Honestly,

218
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,960
if I wasn't there with someone you sent,

219
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:10,680
I wouldn't dare be alone with that woman.

220
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,720
She's the one who drugged us.

221
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:16,480
Anong is the most dangerous person.

222
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:18,800
I'm sure of it.

223
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:20,440
She's seriously unsettling.

224
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:23,480
Why don't we just call the police
and end this?

225
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:27,440
Even Mr. Warat searched the house,

226
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,200
but he still couldn't find anything.

227
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:30,560
That's true.

228
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,960
But I'm more interested
in the motive behind it.

229
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:39,080
I want to know too
how Kluay and Anong are connected.

230
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:42,080
That's the question.

231
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:46,080
But every time someone digs into this,

232
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:48,280
someone gets hurt or ends up dead.

233
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:54,560
Like my dad.

234
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:58,320
That means Ms. Kluay

235
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:02,280
must be extremely important to Anong,
important enough to kill for.

236
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:07,359
I have to find out. There must be a way.

237
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:11,079
And we have to find out quickly
before she realizes.

238
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:12,960
Arnon, do you remember

239
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,440
Pong and Soi? The ones I told you about.

240
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:19,880
They used to work
at Mr. Sarut's old company.

241
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:23,240
My team is investigating them too.

242
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,880
I'm sure it's all connected.

243
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:33,240
Aunt Nong.

244
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,440
Aunt Nong.

245
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:37,840
Please stop stressing.
I already promised you

246
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:40,600
I'd make sure Warat
inherits everything as soon as possible.

247
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:45,520
But will it be in time, Sin?
If Warat finds out…

248
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:46,960
Then what? Even if he knows,

249
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:48,720
all he can do is keep quiet.

250
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:50,600
A nobody like him can't do anything.

251
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:51,960
He's just a lover's child.

252
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,800
A lover's child?

253
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:57,440
How many times have I warned you?

254
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:58,960
Doesn't it get through your head?

255
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:01,040
Don't call Warat that again.

256
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,520
- Who do you think you are?!
- Sin!

257
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,480
- What? Come on then.
- Sin.

258
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:06,720
- Sin.
- Come at me if you dare.

259
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,120
Sin, don't.

260
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:10,760
Sin, look at me.

261
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,000
I'm fine.

262
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:13,480
It didn't hit me.

263
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:14,760
Auntie!

264
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,960
Mr. Rut, please go outside.

265
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:19,120
Why are you backing down?

266
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,240
He was going to kill us.

267
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:21,640
- Sin.
- Yeah. Come on.

268
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:23,120
Come on.

269
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:29,640
Sin.

270
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,600
Good, Anong.

271
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,840
At least you still have your senses.

272
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:51,520
Clean everything up properly.

273
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:53,680
Yes.

274
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:05,880
I saw it with my own eyes

275
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:11,080
that Ampha
took Waree and ran away with Pong.

276
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:17,280
If I had known

277
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:21,760
that would be the last day
I'd ever see Waree,

278
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:25,720
I would have told you to stop them.

279
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:28,120
But at least it's a good thing

280
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:32,440
that Ms. Kluay confirmed
Miss Waree is still alive.

281
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:36,720
Then why won't you tell me the truth?

282
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:41,280
I've asked you so many times
about Ampha and Waree.

283
00:19:41,360 --> 00:19:43,480
And you always give the same answer.

284
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,440
That they're missing.

285
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:51,520
With the utmost respect, ma'am, I take
full responsibility for this matter.

286
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:52,520
Back then,

287
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:56,000
I had people searching everywhere
for Ms. Ampha and Miss Waree.

288
00:19:56,080 --> 00:19:58,520
But then
Mr. Wichan was diagnosed with cancer,

289
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,880
and you also fell ill.

290
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:03,560
I had to close the matter quickly.

291
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:06,560
So I told you
that both of them had gone missing.

292
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,280
But now,

293
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:13,360
Boonsita has confirmed
that Waree is still alive.

294
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:16,560
What are you going to do next?

295
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:20,000
I will find her, no matter what.

296
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:22,200
I will not make
the same mistake twice, ma'am.

297
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,920
What about Warat?

298
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:27,440
What should we do about him?

299
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:30,960
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

300
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:34,520
no one can escape the truth.

301
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:41,240
Ugh. In the end, the two of us

302
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,680
don't even know who we really are.

303
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:45,920
Same fate.

304
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:50,360
When I heard Grandma and Mr. Supol saying

305
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:55,120
that the break-in at Baan Saeng was
because of me, I was confused too.

306
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:01,400
So the reason
you've all been acting strange

307
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:03,440
is because of this, right?

308
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:06,520
You, Mr. Arnon,

309
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:08,680
and Som too.

310
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,040
Mama Toi knows about this as well, right?

311
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:16,760
Is that why no one would let me
go back to Baan Saeng?

312
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:20,880
Kluay, everyone is worried about you.

313
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:22,400
Don't overthink it.

314
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:29,800
But I probably
won't be staying here much longer.

315
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:31,800
Why?

316
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:33,920
Because your grandmother

317
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:36,360
is afraid you'll get caught
in the crossfire like Mr. Arnon.

318
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:40,200
She'll probably have Mr. Supol come talk
to me about leaving this place.

319
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:45,000
Do you think I'd let her do that?

320
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:47,400
Your grandmother is right.

321
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:50,320
You're her only grandchild.

322
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:54,840
How could she let you risk your life
for someone she doesn't even know?

323
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:57,000
Once the DNA results come out,

324
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,600
you might change your mind, Kluay.

325
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:11,040
Sin, wait. Sin, wait for me.

326
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:18,160
Aunt Nong, don't try to persuade me
to apologize to Uncle Rut.

327
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,040
This time, I did nothing wrong.

328
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,960
I understand, but…

329
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,880
Didn't we already agree, Sin?

330
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:29,520
That we would do everything
for your mother?

331
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:33,280
So she can finally rest in peace.

332
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:36,400
You haven't forgotten, have you?

333
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:40,120
I haven't, Auntie.

334
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:44,080
I'll do everything I promised you.

335
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:47,840
But I will never make peace
with someone who sees us as trash.

336
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,120
Sin.

337
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:51,480
Uncle Rut doesn't think that way.

338
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:53,360
He raised you.

339
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:56,680
You were able to graduate and you have
a good job today. Isn't it because of him?

340
00:22:56,760 --> 00:22:59,800
He only did that
so I would get close to Warat for him.

341
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:02,960
Don't worry, Auntie.

342
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:06,080
I'll keep my promise.

343
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,680
Okay? Is that enough?

344
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:13,480
Hearing that puts my mind at ease.

345
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:15,800
Here, Sin,

346
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:18,120
take this and eat it in the car.

347
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:19,840
And tomorrow,

348
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:23,360
come have breakfast together like usual.

349
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:24,520
So Uncle Rut won't ask about you.

350
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:26,280
Someone like him would ask about me?

351
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:34,040
Alright, Auntie. Then

352
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:36,240
I'll head to work now.

353
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:40,120
Drive safely.

354
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:50,520
You haven't even looked at it yet?

355
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:52,280
I trust you.

356
00:23:52,360 --> 00:23:55,560
- Is that not good?
- Two brains are better than one.

357
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:58,960
You were in that meeting. You know
Mr. Warat is trying to take us down.

358
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:01,600
Just go easy on him.
No need to humiliate him.

359
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:03,200
What do you mean?

360
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:07,040
Go with it. Losing once isn't a big deal.
You've been winning all along.

361
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:10,600
What's wrong with you?

362
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:13,480
So you want me to go out there
and lose on purpose?

363
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:20,120
This is a deal I didn't disclose
in the last meeting.

364
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:23,320
It may have caused some executives

365
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:26,960
to misunderstand my intentions
and Mr. Jirasin's.

366
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:30,520
In the next file, this is Mr. Tony.

367
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:35,280
Mr. Tony is a dealer who can get
our products onto shelves in Singapore.

368
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:38,440
If we succeed,

369
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:40,440
our revenue forecast for the next quarter

370
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:43,440
could grow by up to 30%.

371
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,800
If the deal is this good,

372
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:49,920
why did you handle it so secretly before?

373
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:52,280
So we could see the intention…

374
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:53,400
It wasn't certain yet.

375
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:55,960
And we didn't know
what changes might happen.

376
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:59,000
This deal is…

377
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:01,640
It's a very sensitive one.

378
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:04,320
If you failed and announced it,

379
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:07,920
it could have distorted
the company's revenue.

380
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:11,560
Yes, ma'am.
I sincerely apologize for doing that.

381
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:13,040
Well…

382
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:17,400
I must also thank Mr. Arnon and Mr. Warat

383
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:20,280
for helping protect Vanich's interests.

384
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:23,000
There may have been
misunderstandings before.

385
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:24,520
I do apologize.

386
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:26,760
From now on, let's work together
to make Vanich

387
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:29,600
great again like it always has been.

388
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:50,360
I think Jirasin is lucky today.

389
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,880
I postponed my appointment
with Grandma, but she refused.

390
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:55,840
Let's set that aside for now.

391
00:25:55,920 --> 00:25:59,000
We can deal with it later.
Right now, the most important thing

392
00:25:59,080 --> 00:26:01,640
is Ms. Kluay.
Because this concerns life and death.

393
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:03,720
But I think Kluay's background

394
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:05,920
is the key right now.

395
00:26:06,520 --> 00:26:08,880
Drinks and snacks are here.

396
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:13,520
Wow, everything looks so good.

397
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:16,920
Everyone,

398
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,680
since Kluay already knows about this,

399
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,520
should we invite her to join us?

400
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:24,120
No. This is too sensitive.

401
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,960
We're outsiders.

402
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:30,080
But if Kluay gets involved,
it's too risky. We shouldn't do it.

403
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:32,080
- I understand.
- Let's continue.

404
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:35,880
I think the best starting point
is Ms. Kluay's background.

405
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:37,040
Yes.

406
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:38,640
Every time something moves forward,

407
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:41,040
someone gets hurt or someone dies.

408
00:26:41,120 --> 00:26:43,280
From my dad,

409
00:26:43,360 --> 00:26:46,400
to Arnon,
and it even reached Kluay herself.

410
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:48,720
I've been thinking.

411
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:51,280
If Kluay dies,

412
00:26:52,240 --> 00:26:53,640
what does Ms. Anong gain?

413
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:56,000
And if Kluay doesn't die,

414
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:57,920
what does Ms. Anong lose?

415
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:02,760
Looking at the present,
there's no clear answer.

416
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:06,040
But if we look at Kluay's past,

417
00:27:06,560 --> 00:27:08,640
I think we might find one.

418
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:09,920
I agree.

419
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:11,560
<i>Som's father</i>

420
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:14,160
<i>investigated the car fire incident</i>
<i>involving Ms. Kluay</i>

421
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:15,880
<i>and found that it wasn't an accident.</i>

422
00:27:15,960 --> 00:27:19,000
<i>It was staged murder</i>
<i>of the people in the car</i>

423
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:21,040
<i>and Ms. Kluay.</i>

424
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:25,760
Dad did everything
to find out who Kluay really is.

425
00:27:25,840 --> 00:27:27,920
Just when things were progressing,

426
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:31,240
he discovered
that the burned car was illegal.

427
00:27:31,320 --> 00:27:34,800
It had fake registration
and couldn't be traced.

428
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:38,560
Mm.

429
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:41,280
I think the bodies
in that car are the key.

430
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:43,800
Even if we don't know anything else,

431
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:45,960
we do know that

432
00:27:46,480 --> 00:27:49,720
there was one male body
and one female body.

433
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:55,920
Our team is currently investigating
at the unidentified bodies foundation.

434
00:27:56,920 --> 00:28:01,000
Arnon will compare Kluay's DNA
with those two bodies

435
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:01,960
if we find them.

436
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:05,400
That's good. In that case, Som,

437
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:06,960
keep handling the evidence
on Kluay's side.

438
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:08,360
Easy.

439
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:11,680
I just need to pull
one strand of her hair, done.

440
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:15,840
Now, let's think.
How is Anong connected to all this?

441
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,400
Oh, very much connected.

442
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:19,160
Let's assume this.

443
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:21,960
Assume the people

444
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:23,360
who broke into Baan Saeng

445
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,360
<i>were Anong's people.</i>
<i>The one who drugged me</i>

446
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:27,720
was Anong.

447
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:30,640
And the one who drugged Kluay
was also Anong.

448
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:33,880
When we started getting close
to her secret,

449
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:36,120
she decided to get rid of us.

450
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:37,600
And another assumption.

451
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:41,400
Let's assume that your father

452
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:43,960
was attacked and killed by…

453
00:28:44,560 --> 00:28:46,120
It could have been

454
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:48,560
Anong's doing too.

455
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,600
Yes.

456
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:52,520
And it lines up perfectly.

457
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:54,600
I checked the people
around Anong and Mr. Sarut

458
00:28:54,680 --> 00:28:58,160
who disappeared
around the time of the fire.

459
00:28:58,240 --> 00:29:00,280
Who were they?

460
00:29:00,360 --> 00:29:02,120
You'll be shocked.

461
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:05,080
Pong and Soi.

462
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:09,360
Those two.

463
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:11,200
Kluay once saw a vision from the past

464
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:13,040
<i>that they took Ms. Ampha and her daughter</i>

465
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:14,640
away from the Vanich house.

466
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:16,000
Really?

467
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:18,120
Now all that's left is the DNA test

468
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:20,280
to see whether those two
are the bodies in the car.

469
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:22,040
Ameena's maid

470
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:24,040
is Pong's older sister.

471
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:26,320
She's been trying to find out

472
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:29,640
what happened to her brother too.

473
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:34,560
If everything goes as we think,

474
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:37,520
then it means

475
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:40,760
Kluay is the daughter of…

476
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:02,080
No need to bring me anything else.

477
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:03,320
I'm full.

478
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:05,200
But Madam ordered

479
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:08,160
that since you've just recovered,
we must take good care of you.

480
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:11,200
Grandma?

481
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:12,320
Yes.

482
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:26,240
Oh.

483
00:30:27,520 --> 00:30:28,800
Hello, Grandma.

484
00:30:29,320 --> 00:30:30,400
Hello, Mr. Supol.

485
00:30:31,040 --> 00:30:33,880
Such an obedient girl.

486
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:35,800
I told you to stay home and rest,

487
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:37,960
and you really stayed all day.

488
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:42,400
Actually, I came down this morning,
but no one was around.

489
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:46,040
So I called Warat and found out

490
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:49,080
you both had a big meeting,
so I didn't want to disturb you.

491
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:51,760
Are you feeling better now?

492
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:55,920
Yes, but I still feel a bit dizzy.

493
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:59,080
You and Arnon are very lucky.

494
00:30:59,160 --> 00:31:02,520
You already know
what kind of poison it was, right?

495
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:04,080
Yes.

496
00:31:04,600 --> 00:31:06,080
It was deadly.

497
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:08,080
Supol

498
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:10,920
has something important
to discuss with you.

499
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:13,520
I need to go upstairs
to clear some work first.

500
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:15,040
- Supol.
- Yes, ma'am.

501
00:31:15,120 --> 00:31:16,720
Handle it properly.

502
00:31:17,280 --> 00:31:18,160
Yes, ma'am.

503
00:31:25,480 --> 00:31:26,600
Please have a seat.

504
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:38,840
Hello?

505
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:42,200
How is it? Are the results out yet?

506
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:45,360
Uh…

507
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:47,840
It's been sent by email?

508
00:31:48,360 --> 00:31:50,400
I'm not home right now.

509
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:52,560
I'll check it when I get back.

510
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:55,920
But could I get a paper copy as well?

511
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:57,520
An official document.

512
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,400
Okay, okay.

513
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:04,680
Uh,

514
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:07,760
I have something urgent to attend to.

515
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,040
You two can continue talking.

516
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:10,480
Alright.

517
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:19,400
This is a token of appreciation
from Madam.

518
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:21,200
Mr. Supol,

519
00:32:21,280 --> 00:32:24,000
I can't give you an answer right now.

520
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:28,960
If you've heard about Ms. Ampha's spirit,

521
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:33,240
then you should know that Warat and I

522
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:35,840
promised to help her no matter what.

523
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:37,680
I understand

524
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:42,320
that Madam's order
may go against both of your intentions.

525
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:47,920
Then how are we supposed to help Ms. Ampha
if we're not allowed to be involved?

526
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:52,520
In that case,
may I discuss this with Warat first?

527
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,520
Uh…

528
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:58,160
Please try to understand Warat.

529
00:32:58,240 --> 00:33:01,040
You know the reason

530
00:33:01,120 --> 00:33:03,840
why he has to investigate
his parents like this, right?

531
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:08,840
If Grandma had told the truth
from the beginning,

532
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,720
this would have been over already.

533
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:13,400
What about that?

534
00:33:14,120 --> 00:33:17,960
I've tried talking to Grandma many times,

535
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:19,160
but it didn't work.

536
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:20,280
Alright.

537
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:22,840
Then I'll report back to Madam

538
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:25,080
that you'd like
to consult Mr. Warat first.

539
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:28,360
Thank you very much.

540
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:31,440
Has Mr. Warat not returned yet?

541
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:32,560
Uh.

542
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:05,080
I've called you so many times.
Was your phone on silent?

543
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:10,040
Are the DNA results out?

544
00:34:10,120 --> 00:34:12,760
Can you guess what the result is?

545
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:15,520
Mr. Warat…

546
00:34:16,960 --> 00:34:18,000
It's fine.

547
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:20,120
I'm okay.

548
00:34:20,199 --> 00:34:22,600
I'm glad to hear that.

549
00:34:23,639 --> 00:34:26,199
But this is something big.

550
00:34:26,280 --> 00:34:28,880
If you can't handle it,
you don't have to force yourself.

551
00:34:30,199 --> 00:34:31,199
Me? Forcing myself?

552
00:34:32,280 --> 00:34:35,600
The DNA results between you and…

553
00:34:35,679 --> 00:34:37,800
Mr. Sarut and I are not related.

554
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:40,800
There's no blood relation at all.

555
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:43,440
He's not my father.

556
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:45,360
Want to see it? It's in the file.

557
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:48,159
No, it's okay. I don't need to see it.

558
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:51,080
But are you really okay?

559
00:34:51,679 --> 00:34:53,320
I'm okay. But something feels off.

560
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:57,040
Like something doesn't add up,

561
00:34:57,680 --> 00:34:59,120
but I can't tell what it is.

562
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:12,000
Mm. Come in.

563
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:16,720
This morning,

564
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:19,440
Sin came to apologize to you repeatedly.

565
00:35:19,520 --> 00:35:23,280
He said he didn't mean
to avoid you earlier.

566
00:35:23,360 --> 00:35:25,800
He just had to rush to work.

567
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:28,160
I don't hold it against him.

568
00:35:28,240 --> 00:35:29,240
I understand.

569
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:32,680
Everyone is just doing their duty.

570
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:35,400
Sin understands that too.

571
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:37,200
We'll see about that.

572
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:39,280
Oh.

573
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,360
Here.

574
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:44,360
I just replaced your toothbrush.

575
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:47,440
Why are you asking for a new one again?

576
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:49,640
The old one is worn out,

577
00:35:49,720 --> 00:35:51,160
so I ordered a new one.

578
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:56,160
Alright, if you're done here,
go do whatever you need to do.

579
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:20,720
I suppose we'll have to rely on
what you've prepared, dear.

580
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,960
UNIDENTIFIED BODIES FOUNDATION

581
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:34,680
Time to eat.

582
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:38,120
Put that away, Mom. It's time to eat.

583
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:40,240
I didn't help you at all.

584
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,760
About Kluay,

585
00:36:41,840 --> 00:36:44,920
the more we dig,
the more strange things we find.

586
00:36:46,280 --> 00:36:50,360
Now I understand why your dad
couldn't let this go back then.

587
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:52,560
Seeing all this,

588
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:55,360
we have to finish what he left unfinished.

589
00:36:56,640 --> 00:36:57,720
That's right.

590
00:36:57,800 --> 00:37:00,520
I've arranged a team to run DNA tests

591
00:37:00,600 --> 00:37:03,400
on Pong, Soi, and the housemaid.

592
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:05,840
That sounds promising.

593
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:08,640
But it'll probably take years.

594
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:10,680
What should we do, Mom?

595
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:14,280
That's what worries me.

596
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:17,320
For me, it's fine.

597
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:20,960
But now that we know this isn't normal,

598
00:37:21,040 --> 00:37:24,400
I'm ready to fight.

599
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:28,400
I'm just worried about the kids
at Baan Saeng, and Kluay and Som.

600
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:29,840
Hearing you say that,

601
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:34,520
as a business partner
and the head of security,

602
00:37:34,600 --> 00:37:36,120
I feel a bit hurt.

603
00:37:36,200 --> 00:37:37,440
Oh.

604
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:41,440
Som and I just didn't want to bother you.

605
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:44,720
We didn't mean to upset you.

606
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:45,920
Please don't overthink it.

607
00:37:46,680 --> 00:37:50,880
A few days
or even a couple of weeks is fine.

608
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:53,480
But this will take months at least.

609
00:37:53,560 --> 00:37:56,760
You can't keep driving back and forth
between here and your house.

610
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:59,240
If it's convenient for you two,

611
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:00,560
I'm more than willing.

612
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:04,480
But if it's not, I'll assign

613
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:08,280
a team to handle security
as tightly as before.

614
00:38:09,040 --> 00:38:10,600
Oh my.

615
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:11,520
Hm.

616
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:13,880
Who would be heartless enough to refuse?

617
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:15,880
If you're willing,

618
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:18,560
I'm really grateful.

619
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:20,520
Thank you, Arnon.

620
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:22,480
I'll do my best.

621
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:29,880
Are you really going to do
what Grandma said?

622
00:38:34,560 --> 00:38:37,440
<i>Does Mr. Warat suspect</i>
<i>we harmed his woman,</i>

623
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:39,160
so he came to search our house?

624
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:41,000
I'm not entirely sure.

625
00:38:42,120 --> 00:38:44,480
<i>I didn't come here to cause trouble.</i>

626
00:38:44,560 --> 00:38:47,640
Today, I came with good intentions.

627
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:51,920
Don't worry about me.
I can take care of myself.

628
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:56,760
<i>Soon, the Vanich family</i>
<i>will pay for everything</i>

629
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:58,240
<i>they've done to us.</i>

630
00:38:58,840 --> 00:38:59,960
And when that time comes,

631
00:39:01,080 --> 00:39:02,760
I'll laugh right in their faces.

632
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:31,560
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
